&lt;DIV&gt;#1: Give warriors a permanent further increase in damage mitigation and avoidance, so that the remain clearly the best choice for tanking nameds. &lt;FONT color=#9933ff&gt;(They already are, why retune every past encounter for the same end result?) ...&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;#2: Rebalance named mobs by reducing the DB and DI....&amp;nbsp;&lt;FONT color=#cc00ff&gt; &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;FONT color=#9933ff&gt;again, retune for what ~ this also gives us the same end result as is currently in game.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;#3: Compensate the loss of defensive/evasive from the warrior's ability set by giving them some abilities that allow them to contribute to the group in places where the warrior's superior ability to take damage is rendered irrelevant and useless.&amp;nbsp; &lt;FONT color=#9933ff&gt;(I agree with this part).&lt;/FONT&gt;&amp;nbsp; After all, in most groups, as long as the tank can take damage "well enough" to not die, they don't really care HOW much better he is than the next guy. This is why you hear beastlords, rangers, and monks tanking in groups in content that is considered trivial. They tank "well enough", but they add significantly to the group in other ways.&amp;nbsp; &lt;FONT color=#6633ff&gt;In most of the content I am currently doing, the non-highenduber-raid BL Monk or Ranger cannot tank effectively for XP groups.&lt;/FONT&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;FONT color=#6633ff&gt;I often group with a war.&amp;nbsp; She will DPS while I tank, we ping-pong a lot of the time.&amp;nbsp; I would in fact like her to have higher DPS when she is not tanking, but this is a totally other forum that has also been beaten to death.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
